<h2>
    Top Lakes and Reservoirs for Bass Fishing
</h2>
<h3>
    Emigrant Lake
</h3>
<p>
    Located 10 minutes from Medford, this large reservoir offers outstanding largemouth action around submerged trees, coves, and drop-offs.
</p>
<h3>
    Agate Lake
</h3>
<p>
    This shallow lake warms quickly, making it a springtime favorite. Fish near lily pads and cattails using frogs, worms, or jigs.
</p>
<h3>
    Willow Lake
</h3>
<p>
    A scenic spot near Butte Falls, Willow Lake offers solid largemouth fishing and shoreline access, plus camping amenities.
</p>
<h3>
    Applegate Lake
</h3>
<p>
    While more popular for trout, Applegate supports a solid smallmouth population, especially near rocky points and dam structures.
</p>
